Package com.cafean.CalcServer.rpc

Class CalcServerRequester

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.rpc.AbstractRPCConnection
      • com.cafean.rpc.RPCRequester
        • com.cafean.CalcServer.rpc.AbstractServerRequester
          • com.cafean.CalcServer.rpc.CalcServerRequester
  • public class CalcServerRequester
extends AbstractServerRequester
    The custom Calculation Server requestor object used to interact directly with a server. This class encapsulates all communication with the server from the client side. This includes methods for each RPC call.

    All RPC methods in this class that do not return an RPCResponse may return RPCResponse.COMM_FAILURE to indicate that the connection failed during the request and could not be re-established.

        public int mountRootFolder​(java.io.File folder,
                           java.lang.String alias,
                           java.awt.Window parent)
        Requests that the calculation server mount the given folder as a root folder with the given alias. If the request fails a message dialog will be displayed indicating the reason for the failure.

      • sendFileBegin

        public int sendFileBegin​(java.lang.String name,
                         java.lang.String location,
                         boolean overwrite)
        Requests that a file transfer begin for the given file, location, etc.
        Parameters:
        name - a String containing the desired name of the file on the target system
        location - a String containing the full folder path (including root folder) to the desired location on the target system
        overwrite - true if an existing file should be overwritten
        Returns:
        the newly allocated "file id" for the file being transferred; -1 destination folder does not exist; -2 No write permission to the destination; -3 This file is already being transferred; -4 File already exists; -5 Failed to create file for request; -6 Failed to open file for request

      • sendFileChunk

        public int sendFileChunk​(int fileID,
                         byte[] contents,
                         int length,
                         boolean complete)
        appends the given contents to the file transfer in progress with the given file id
        Parameters:
        fileID - the id returned from sendFileBegin(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, boolean).
        contents - a byte[] containing a segment of the file to be sent
        length - the number of bytes in content that should be sent

        Returns:
